Despite the grueling tour schedule that followed the ongoing success of the record, Michael found time for two notable studio collaborations. In 2012, he hit the studio with Black Keys' Dan Auerbach to record a new b-side, 'Lasan', for his Getting Ready single, and in 2013, Michael was invited by Jack White to record at his Nashville studios where the pair laid down two tracks: a new song, You've Got Nothing To Lose, and a cover of Town Van Zandt's 'Waitin' Round To Die. The tracks were released in Spring 2014 on 7" vinyl as part of White's Third Man Records' Blue Series.
